-----------------------------------------------------------------------
2008
-----------------------------------------------------------------------

 8 Feb - Released version 2.0 of Invar.
14 Feb - Changed definition of $InvarDirectory. It was assuming a
         single-user installation of xAct. Thanks to Alessandro Stecchina
         for reporting this problem. This is version 2.0.1.
 5 Mar - InvarDoc.nb moved to the Documentation/English subdirectory.
       - Changed MathLink->True from ToCanonical to CanonicalPerm, as
         this option is now in xPerm instead of xTensor. This is version
         2.0.2.

-----------------------------------------------------------------------
2011
-----------------------------------------------------------------------

30 Sep - Added messages mentioning the nonstandard configuration choices
	 of Invar. Reported by Teake and others.
	 This is now version 2.0.3.

23 Oct - Fixed cases g[a,b]Ricci[-a,-b] and g[a,b]Riemann[-a,-c,-b,c]
	 reported by Teake by adding a ContractMetric.
       - Hack to compensate the fact that epsilons are now sorted at
	 the beginning by xTensor, because they have much symmetry,
	 instead of at the end, as Invar always wanted.
	 Rerelease version 2.0.3.

